{{wikipedia}}

===Etymology===
Sense of “what is {{l|en|added}}” dates from 14th century, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|adition||increasement|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|additiōnem}}, accusative singular of {{term|additio|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/əˈdɪʃn̩/|/əˈdɪʃən/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-addition.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|ɪʃən|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{context|uncountable|lang=en}} The act of adding anything.
#: ''The addition of five more items to the agenda will make the meeting unbearably long.''
# Anything that is added.
# {{context|uncountable|lang=en}} The [[arithmetic operation]] of [[add]]ing.
# {{context|music|lang=en}} A dot at the right side of a note as an indication that its sound is to be lengthened one half.
# {{context|legal|lang=en}} A [[title]] annexed to a person's name to identify him or her more precisely, as in "John Doe, '''Esq'''.", "Robert Dale, '''Mason'''", "Thomas Way, '''of New York'''".
# {{context|heraldry|lang=en}} Something added to a coat of arms, as a mark of honour; opposed to {{term|abatement|lang=en}}.

